original_title: NPP, SJB, NDF win seats in Kalutara District
original_body_lines: The Election Commission of Sri Lanka has released the final results of the Kalutara District in the 2024 General Election with the National People’s Power (NPP) polling more than 66% of the total votes in the district.
NPP has polled 452,398 votes to win the district while the Samagi Jana Balawegaya (SJB) is second with 53,200 votes (18.84%).
Accordingly, the NPP has secured 8 seats in the district while the SJB has won two seats and the NDF a single seat in the district.
